video.title: Last Chance U
video.synopsis: Elite athletes with difficult pasts turn to junior college football for a last shot at turning their lives around and achieving their dreams.

episodes.synopsis: Desperate for an opportunity at a major school, the players at East Mississippi Community College prepare for a season that's crucial to their future.
episodes.title: Last Chance U

episodes.synopsis: The starting quarterback battle rages on. Brittany worries about the players' academic progress. EMCC's winning streak is threatened by a rival.
episodes.title: Most Dangerous Game

episodes.synopsis: The coaches and players deal with unfamiliar adversity. DJ and others struggle with school. Ollie faces tough times and seeks comfort back home.
episodes.title: Plan B

episodes.synopsis: Players, other students and the community prepare for homecoming weekend. Tensions rise at the homecoming game, prompting Buddy to lose his cool.
episodes.title: Homecoming

episodes.synopsis: DJ faces choices that will make or break his future. John hopes for a chance to impress Auburn coaches. Bad blood builds in the regular-season finale.
episodes.title: Blood Makes the Grass Grow

episodes.synopsis: The regular season comes to an explosive end, and the team must deal with the fallout from their actions. The players prepare for life after EMCC.
episodes.title: It Is What It Is

episodes.synopsis: Buddy makes changes in response to the publicity the show brought to the EMCC program. The Lions are forced to play short-handed in the season opener.
episodes.title: Half a Team

episodes.synopsis: De'Andre gears up for his first game since he was kicked out of Florida State. Isaiah and his brother open up about their difficult childhood.
episodes.title: Football Saved My Life

episodes.synopsis: Brittany and Davern try to motivate Kam on and off the field. Isaiah's health concerns continue into a rivalry game against Itawamba.
episodes.title: Can't Make the Club in the Tub

episodes.synopsis: Faith takes center stage as Buddy, Dakota and others explore the role of religion in their football journey. A much-awaited rematch approaches.
episodes.title: Ain't It a Sin

episodes.synopsis: As EMCC prepares for the No. 1 team in the country, defensive linemen Chauncey, Kam and Tim continue their battle to atone for their past actions.
episodes.title: For My Momma

episodes.synopsis: EMCC hopes to maintain its focus against winless Coahoma, a program trying to overcome a deficiency in talent, facilities and support.
episodes.title: The Curse

episodes.synopsis: As the state playoffs loom, tensions rise between several players and the coaches. Brittany ponders her future at EMCC.
episodes.title: Bigger and Better Things

episodes.synopsis: It's crunch time as the players take finals and weigh scholarship offers while still holding aspirations of winning a national championship at EMCC.
episodes.title: Last Man Standing

episodes.synopsis: After decades of losing, Independence Community College looks to brash coach Jason Brown to develop a winning culture and recruit talented athletes.
episodes.title: We Expect

episodes.synopsis: After the rough season opener, Coach Brown questions his D1 transfers. Malik and Carlos face tough love as they fight to meet expectations.
episodes.title: Humble Your Pie

episodes.synopsis: Bad blood with his old boss fuels Brown's fire as the newly confident Pirates welcome defending national champion Garden City to Independence.
episodes.title: Jimmys and Joes

episodes.synopsis: Despite ICC's winning streak, tensions start to boil over as Brown gets fed up with his players and coaches before and during a game in Dodge City.
episodes.title: Get Outta Dodge

episodes.synopsis: Brown and his players open up about their upbringings and how their relationships with family -- positive and negative -- shaped who they are today.
episodes.title: Out of State

episodes.synopsis: The team prepares to play during the town's big annual festival. Bobby struggles to overcome frustration. An ICC student writes a song for the team.
episodes.title: Neewollah

episodes.synopsis: As the Pirates get ready for a shot at a conference title, recruiters from four-year schools visit and players scramble to get their grades in order.
episodes.title: Abracadabra

episodes.synopsis: As a game against rival Coffeyville caps off the regular season, the ICC players and coaches reflect on the season and weigh their next moves.
episodes.title: Dust in The Wind

episodes.synopsis: Jason Brown copes with his celebrity status. Bobby Bruce tries to rebound from bad decisions. Brown considers bringing back a polarizing player.
episodes.title: Dream U

episodes.synopsis: Bobby gets close with Kailon, who tries to keep Bobby on the right path. Assistant coach Jason Martin talks about moving his family into a dorm room.
episodes.title: The Eye in the Sky

episodes.synopsis: The town of Independence gets ready for the highly anticipated home opener. Visits with Chance’s and Kailon’s families shed light on their upbringings.
episodes.title: Home on the Range

episodes.synopsis: Hard feelings from last year rise to the surface in a rematch between ICC and Garden City, as coaches Jason Brown and Jeff Sims butt heads yet again.
episodes.title: Garden City

episodes.synopsis: Jay’s injuries cause him frustration. Malik tries to make the most of his opportunities. Tensions run high after a game against Fort Scott.
episodes.title: The Hangover

episodes.synopsis: As players and coaches start to prioritize themselves over the team, Brown tries to regain control -- but a sideline outburst proves costly.
episodes.title: S Show

episodes.synopsis: Locals grow restless over the team's performance amid budget cuts at ICC. A home game during the "Neewollah" festival could help unite the town.
episodes.title: Famous Forever

episodes.synopsis: The season finale presents a chance to end the season on a positive note. Markiese makes a big mistake, and Brown faces criticism over a text message.
episodes.title: Hustlers Survive

episodes.synopsis: Life is demanding for players at Oakland's Laney College, where they must pay for their own housing and expenses while pursuing a future in football.
episodes.title: The Town

episodes.synopsis: After 40 years, coach John Beam's legacy in Oakland is unmatched. Injuries lead to an unorthodox solution at QB as Laney looks to get back on track.
episodes.title: QB4

episodes.synopsis: Dior's strained relationship with his father affects his play and his health. Nu'u balances school, football and childcare while his wife works.
episodes.title: Cast-Offs

episodes.synopsis: RJ lives for football, but is haunted by an infamous family history. Beam's old school ways don't always connect with the younger generation.
episodes.title: Greyhaven

episodes.synopsis: Rejzohn discusses a painful memory, then suffers a physical setback. Despite recent success, Laney still feels disrespected by a rival in San Francisco.
episodes.title: The City

episodes.synopsis: As Dior looks for a way out of California, Beam questions if Nu'u could commit to moving his family away from Oakland. RJ's frustrations mount.
episodes.title: Ā, upane! ka upane!

episodes.synopsis: Gentrification in Oakland brings some positive changes, but pushes longtime residents out of the city. The Eagles begin a late push for a playoff bid.
episodes.title: New Oakland

episodes.synopsis: As the season winds down, the graduating players plan their next moves while Beam pledges to make changes and build an even better team next year.
episodes.title: Football might be over for you
